race.comment: DEEL ME A QUEEN (6) started warm favourite but only ground away to finish fourth last start over 1450m at this track. Gets to this distance for the first time but on breeding and racing style it looks a good move. In the right race to bounce back for supporters. SWEET BUBBLES (1) won a similar race here two back then stepped up in grade at Newcastle last start and struggled. Freshened up and worth another chance back in her right race. OBVIOUSLY ALBERT (9) has only won once in 26 runs but recent efforts have been encouraging. Made late inroads to get up for second last time over the mile at Nowra. This step up in distance comes at the perfect time. BUMP'N'RUN (3) did his best work late when runner-up in open company over 1600m at Taree last start. Big drop in grade and this looks a nice assignment at the third run back. CASSIE'S LAD (4) on a 48-hour back-up will be popular with punters.
